		</head>
			<div type="textpart" subtype="work">
			<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.hypermenes.hypermenis_fragmenta.de_chio">
			ΠΕΡΙ ΧΙΟΥ
			</ref></title></ab>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="1">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen quartum#urn:lofts:fhg.4.hypermenes.hypermenis_fragmenta.de_chio:1">
					<bibl> Ptolemaeus Hephaest. Lib. VI, p. 197 ed. Westerm.:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Ὑπερμένης ἐν τῷ Περὶ Χίου, Ὁμήρου φησὶ γενέσθαι θεράποντα Σκινδαψὸν ὀνόματι· καὶ τοῦτον ζημιωθῆναι ὑπὸ Χίων χιλίας δραχμὰς διὰ τὸ μὴ καῦσαι τελευτήσαντα τὸν δεσπότην. Ὁ δὲ τὸ ὄργανον εὑρὼν τὸ οὕτω καλούμενον σκινδαψὸν, Ἐρέτριος, ἦν, Ποικίλης αὐλητρίδος υἱός.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"> Hypermenes in libro De Chio narrat Homeri famulum fuisse Scindapsum, eique muletam mille drachmarum a Chiis irrogatam esse, quod corpus domini defuncti non cremasset. Ille vero Scindapsus, qui cognominis instrumenti inventor fuit, Eretriensis est, Poeciles tibicinis filius. </note>
					<note type="commentary">(Cf. Athen. IV, cap. 81; XIV, p. 636, B. Lobeck. Aglaoph. p. 1331 et quam laudat Mannerti dissert. De Scindapso.) Hypermenem Chium et rhapsodum fuisse opinatur Coray. in Ἀτάκτ. III, 243. Welcker. In Cycl. ep. p. 177, eundem esse putat cum Euthymene, quem laudat Clem. Alex. Strom. I, p. 141, 21 Sylb. (II, p. 80 Klotz.): Εὐθυμένης ἐν τοῖς Χρονικοῖς συνασμάσαντα (sc. τὸν Ὅμηρον) ἐπὶ Ἀκάστου ἐν Χίῳ γενέσθαι περὶ τὸ διακοσιοστὸν ἔτος ὕστερον τῆς Ἰλίου ἁλώσεως (φησίν).</note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
